Arbitrary Pricing Theory(APT)
Unlike the CAPM, the APT does not assume the investors invest on effecient portfolios. 
The APT has 3 underlying assumptions:

Specific Risk can be eliminated by divisification;
There are no arbitrary opportunity for the investors, if any, will soon disapear;
Asset returns can be explained by systematic factors;

